  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is being undertaken to understand how a gastric bypass can affect a subject's
      diabetes even prior to their losing significant amounts of weight. The hypothesis of this
      study is that increased glucagon-like peptide-1 (GLP-1) secretion explains the amelioration
      in insulin secretion after Roux-en-Y Gastric Bypass (RYGB) surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
